Workshop organized by Keith & Jess

From The Ground Up:

From the ground up represents footwork as a foundation. Also a metaphor for being rooted into the earth. Knowing that anytime you need to begin again your start by planting the seed of footwork.

Footwork:
We will offer Popping footwork foundation/traditions and ways to create new patterns through application.

Floorwork:
It‚Äôs easy to think of the floor as just blow ups. We will share how to play with rhythms on the floor to help you make your floor game feel like your dancing on your feet. We will offer foundation/traditional shoot downs and variations.

Presentation:
How fashion, style and character play an important role in the dance. Understanding and breaking down how it can influence, highlight movement and different parts of the body.

üí• THIS IS OUR VENUE üí•

OJC presents:
Parks n' Pops: Belly of the Beatz 
Street festival & 1v1 popping battle 

TOMORROW Sat, June 8th

@ Earl Bales Amphitheater
 4169 Bathurst St, Toronto ON

Are you curious about the venue? Say no more,
This is a time lapse of our venue/info & how to get there.

The venue includes:
- Bathrooms
- Water fountain (in the community center next door)
- wheelchair lift for accessibility 
- Seating
- brand new stage for dancers
- greenroom for competitors & judges
- FREE Parking on site (first come, first serve) 

Subway transit:

The venue is located about 10 minutes driving from Shephard yonge station and 15 minutes from Sheppard west station (30 min walk). You can also take the 84D from Sheppard- Yonge station 7 stops to Bathurst St, which is 9 mins walking from Earl Bales Park 
Or take the 984 from Sheppard West station Bathurst Street, which is an 8 min walk from Earl Bales Park.

*Sunscreen, bug spray, and water will be provided for all contestants.*
(But bring your own just in case)
* Bring umbrella (prepare for weather bit gets very sunny)
* Bring a refillable water bottle. The community center next door has a water fountain *

We will provide food to contestants in the green room backstage but bring your own as well. It's going to be a long day dancing outdoors, please come prepared.
